Create a Node.js file that will convert the output "Hello World!" into upper-case letters. //npm install upper-case

var http = require('http'); 
 var uc=require('upper-case');
 http.createServer(function(req, res)
 {
res.writeHead (200, {'Content-type': 'text/html'});
res.write(uc.upperCase('Hello World'));
; }).listen(8001);
res.end()
console.log('Web Server 8000 Started');
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Execution Steps -
1) Ensure you have Node.js and npm (Node Package Manager) installed on your system. 
2) Save the corrected code to a file named uppercase.js.
3) Open your terminal or command prompt and navigate to the directory where uppercase.js is located.
4) Run the following command to install the upper-case module: npm install upper-case
5) Once the installation is complete, you can execute the code by running the following command: node uppercase.js
6) You should see the message "Web Server on Port 8001 Started" in the console.
7) You can access the web server by opening a web browser and visiting http://localhost:8001.
